fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.blueprints.config

Class BaseBlueprintsConfig<C extends BaseBlueprintsConfig<C>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.config.BaseConfig<C>
      • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.blueprints.config.BaseBlueprintsConfig<C>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - the "self"-type of this Config
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Config, ImmutableConfig
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BlueprintsNeo4jConfig, BlueprintsTinkerConfig

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class BaseBlueprintsConfig<C extends BaseBlueprintsConfig<C>>
extends BaseConfig<C>
    The base Config that provides utility methods to create generic Blueprints configuration.

    All features are all optional: configuration can be created using all or none of them.

      • withDefault

        @Nonnull
protected C withDefault()
        Defines the mapping to use for the created BlueprintsBackend.

        This mapping corresponds to a simple representation of multi-valued features, by using the AbstractFeatureBean.position().

        NOTE: This is the default mapping.

        Returns:
        this configuration (for chaining)

        Returns a Predicate used to filter the options to be saved in a configuration file, in order to retrieve them in a future execution.
